readme:
Service Usage

This service allows consumers to create an exception referral and specify the reason for the referral.
The referral is an action item that needs to be performed in the provider operational system.

Service Behaviour

A consumer of this service provides the following data:
Party Id
Referral Type
Referral Sub Type
Channel
Status
Departmental Officer
Given Name
Family Name
ID
Created Date
Reason for Referral
Planned Completion Date
Source Business Service
Service Type
Service Sub Type
Service Sate Code
Recipient Business Service
Service Type
Service Sub Type
Service Sate Code
A consumer of this service relies on ESB for an assured delivery and does not accept a response back.

Service Variants

None

Service Dependencies

Service Composition

This service is not a composite service, i.e. it is not composed of other services in the Service Portfolio.

Service Flow

An event is generated by the Service Consumer which invokes the CreateExceptionReferralRequest service on the ESB;
ESB passes the XML message unchanged through to CCMD&S
No response message is supplied
Alternate Flow 1 (AF1)
There are no alternative flows as no response is given and therefore no error is returned.

Transformation

Service State Management Decisions

No state management.
